-- Abu Dhabi May Buy Dubai's 20% Stake in London Stock Exchange, Times Says
-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 2010-12-19T10:45:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/abu-dhabi-may-buy-dubai-s-20-stake-in-london-stock-exchange-times-says.html
Abu Dhabi is in talks to buy the 20
percent stake in  London Stock Exchange Group Plc  owned by Borse
Dubai Ltd., the  Sunday Times  said, without saying where it got
the information.  Abu Dhabi offered $1.5 billion for the stake, according to
the report. The three stock exchanges in the United Arab
Emirates may merge as part of the deal, the report said.  London Stock Exchange spokesman  Alastair Fairbrother 
declined to comment when contacted by telephone today. A 
Borse Dubai spokesman declined to comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Rachel Graham  in London 
